{
  "stem": "10181.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they-- if they had suspicion, they would ask for your identity card, and-- and if you had Jew on it and you didn't wear the star, and it was just too bad for you.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's how they-- that was the next step.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now you said that they were-- threatened to take you to the camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What-- what were you hearing about camps?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's very strange what I heard, because the only camp I heard of-- and this was-- the threat, was a camp called Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was in Austria.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Apparently-- how did I hear about it?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because apparently in Amsterdam, they had rounded up in the ghetto that there was-- the Jews were ghettoized in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a general strike in 1941 over about three days of the dockworkers, and-- and some working-- you know, workers strike, and there was a sort of riot in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, the-- the Dutch Nazi-- you know, the Dutch police and the Nazis went into the ghetto and started beating up the Jews, so the ghetto organized.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some of the men had started beating up the Dutch Nazis, and they chased them out of the ghetto, out of the streets.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It wasn't the ghetto like it was in Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was sort of certain streets, OK?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they chased them out of there, so then the German police had to come and-- to the aid of the-- the Dutch Nazis.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they, in order to-- as a warning, they picked up, I don't know, a couple of hundred-- I think 200 young Dutch Jews and sent them to Mauthausen, and they were killed in Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think that's how I knew about Mauthausen, because word got around, you know, what-- what-- what was happening.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
